headline: Can Dollar General’s (DG) Holiday Marketing Shift Signal Lasting Brand Relevance Among Value Shoppers?
summary: Dollar General recently launched a series of holiday promotions focused on recipe-centric bundle deals, rotating price reductions, and exclusive themed products aimed at helping customers stretch their budgets through the season. New consumer research highlights that nearly three-quarters of U.S. shoppers, especially Millennials and Gen Z, now plan to visit discount retailers like Dollar General for holiday purchases, driven in part by social media influence and a growing demand for value...

headline: It's 'not your grandfather's S&P 500': Strategist's stock picks
summary: Concerns are mounting among investors about an artificial intelligence (AI) bubble and frothy markets. Mariner Wealth Advisors' chief investment strategist and head of equities, Jeff Krumpelman, tells Yahoo Finance that he believes it's time to look at market valuation through a new lens. The strategist addresses bubble concerns and shares some sector picks. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief.
